 making it True in production.\",\n      \"actual\": \"The default value False is set in Flask.default_config (app.py line 194) and copied into the Config dict at init. from_object('default_settings') will re-set it to False (or whatever default_settings defines) if SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE is defined there. from_envvar then overrides it — but only if the env config file explicitly defines SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE. If the env config file omits this key, the value from from_object('default_settings') or the Flask default (False) persists. If any direct assignment app.config['SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE'] = False appears after from_envvar, it overrides the env config silently.\",\n      \"override_chain\": [\n        \"Flask.default_config ImmutableDict (SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=False) loaded at app init via make_config()\",\n        \"from_object('default_settings') overwrites with module/class uppercase attributes\",\n        \"from_envvar('APP_SETTINGS') -> from_pyfile() -> from_object() overwrites with env config file values\",\n        \"app.config['SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE'] = value (direct assignment) overwrites last\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"override_chain\": [\n    \"Flask.default_config (baked into Config dict at app initialization via make_config())\",\n    \"from_object('default_settings') — iterates dir(obj), sets all uppercase keys; includes inherited class attributes\",\n    \"from_envvar('APP_SETTINGS') — reads file path from env var, delegates to from_pyfile() -> from_object(); only keys present in the file are overwritten\",\n    \"app.config['KEY'] = value (direct assignment) — plain dict __setitem__, overwrites unconditionally\"\n  ],\n  \"precedence_mechanism\": \"Config extends dict. Every load method performs in-place dict updates with no merge logic — last write wins unconditionally. from_object (lines 218-254) iterates dir(obj) and sets self[key] = getattr(obj, key) for uppercase keys. from_pyfile (lines 187-216) executes the file in a temporary module namespace then calls from_object on that module. from_envvar (lines 102-124) reads an env var for a file path and delegates to from_pyfile. There is no protection against later calls re-setting keys to defaults.\",\n  \"root_causes\": [\n    \"Call order violation: if from_object('default_settings') is invoked after from_envvar('APP_SETTINGS'), it unconditionally overwrites every key defined in default_settings, including SECRET_KEY and SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE, reverting them to defaults.\",\n    \"Missing keys in env config file: from_envvar/from_pyfile/from_object only sets keys that are present in the env config file. If the env config file does not define SECRET_KEY or SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE, the values from the earlier from_object('default_settings') call persist unchanged.\",\n    \"Direct assignment after from_envvar: any app.config['SECRET_KEY'] = ... or app.config['SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE'] = ... placed after the from_envvar call will silently override the env-specific values, causing defaults to leak if the assigned value is the default.\",\n    \"Inherited class attributes in from_object: if default_settings is a class, dir() includes attributes inherited from parent classes. A production subclass that does not redefine SECRET_KEY will still expose the parent's default value, which from_object will load.\"\n  ],\n  \"fix\": \"Enforce strict call order: (1) app.config.from_object('default_settings') first to establish defaults, (2) app.config.from_envvar('APP_SETTINGS') second to override with environment-specific values, (3) any intentional direct assignments last. Ensure the env config file explicitly defines every key that must be overridden (especially SECRET_KEY and SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE). Never call from_object or set default values after from_envvar. If using class-based configs, explicitly redefine all security-sensitive keys in each subclass rather than relying on inheritance, since from_object loads inherited attributes via dir().\",\n  \"source_files\": [\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/config.py\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/app.py\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/sansio/app.py\"}\n  ],\n  \"key_code_locations\": [\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/config.py\", \"lines\": \"102-124\", \"method\": \"from_envvar — reads env var for file path, delegates to from_pyfile\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/config.py\", \"lines\": \"187-216\", \"method\": \"from_pyfile — executes file in temp module, calls from_object\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/config.py\", \"lines\": \"218-254\", \"method\": \"from_object — iterates dir(obj), sets uppercase keys; last call wins\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/config.py\", \"lines\": \"304-321\", \"method\": \"from_mapping — sets uppercase keys from a mapping\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/app.py\", \"lines\": \"178-210\", \"note\": \"Flask.default_config defines SECRET_KEY=None, SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=False\"},\n    {\"path\": \"src/flask/sansio/app.py\", \"lines\": \"482-496\", \"method\": \"make_config — copies default_config into new Config dict at app init\"}\n  ]\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013GGyVLSki18Ya6JvZyqXUv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The analysis is complete. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Flask Config Drift Analysis\n\n**Override chain** (last write wins — it's a plain dict):\n1. `Flask.default_config` → pre-populated at init via `make_config()`\n2. `from_object('default_settings')` → sets all uppercase attributes from `dir(obj)`, including inherited ones\n3. `from_envvar('APP_SETTINGS')` → reads file path from env var → `from_pyfile()` → `from_object()` → only keys present in the file are updated\n4. `app.config['KEY'] = value` → direct dict assignment, unconditional\n\n**Two drift points identified:**\n\n| Key | Default | Drift cause |\n|-----|---------|-------------|\n| `SECRET_KEY` | `None` (app.py:183) | Defaults leak if: (a) call order is reversed, (b) env config file omits the key, or (c) direct assignment after `from_envvar` |\n| `SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE` | `False` (app.py:194) | Same — especially dangerous since `False` is a valid falsy value that won't trigger obvious errors |\n\n**Root causes:**\n1. **Wrong call order** — `from_object('default_settings')` after `from_envvar` overwrites env values\n2. **Missing keys in env config file** — `from_envvar` only updates keys present in the file; absent keys retain their `from_object` values\n3. **Post-envvar direct assignment** — `app.config['KEY'] = default_value` after `from_envvar` silently reverts to defaults\n4. **Class inheritance via `dir()`** — `from_object` loads inherited class attributes, so a prod subclass without explicit `SECRET_KEY` picks up the parent's default\n\n**Fix:** Strict order — `from_object` first, `from_envvar` second, intentional direct assignments last. Explicitly define all security-critical keys in the env config file."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1928,"cache_read_input_tokens":32713,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1928},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4afb040b-3d38-4b58-a24c-8e0fc23433de","uuid":"3c2a6c5b-b4e2-4662-a085-eee91639a80f"}
